  "prompt": "Which is the best headphone for \"Moto G 2nd gen\"?",
  "response": "Choosing the best headphone for your Moto G 2nd gen largely depends on your preferences for sound quality, design, comfort, and additional features. Here are a few recommendations across different categories that you might consider:\n\n1. **Budget-Friendly Option:**\n   - **Sony MDR-ZX110**: These are affordable, lightweight, and offer decent sound quality for the price.\n\n2. **Wireless Headphones:**\n   - **JBL T450BT**: These Bluetooth headphones offer good sound quality, comfortable fit, and a reasonable price.\n\n3. **In-Ear Headphones:**\n   - **Sennheiser CX 300-II Precision**: These in-ear headphones provide excellent sound quality and are very portable.\n\n4. **Noise-Cancelling Headphones:**\n   - **Sony WH-1000XM4**: If you are looking for great noise-cancellation and high-quality sound, these are top-rated and comfortable to wear.\n\n5. **Workout Headphones:**\n   - **Jabra Elite Active 75t**: These are wireless, durable, sweat-resistant, and offer good sound quality.\n\nSince the Moto G 2nd gen has a 3.5mm headphone jack, all wired headphones will be compatible. For wireless options, ensure they have Bluetooth compatibility. Ensure you verify the compatibility with the device specifications and personal preferences before making a purchase.",
